As I explained, the principle difference between a Hedge Fund and a CTA=20
(Commodity Trading Advisor), is the manner in which they control the assets=20
that they are contracted to manage. In the case of a CTA, the money can not=20
be held by the CTA itself. The underlying investor will open a clearing=20
account with a respective Clearing House, the assets will remain in this=20
account and the CTA will trade based on the full monetary value of that=20
account - in many cases an investor may well fund this account with Notional=
=20
Funding. NF are 'abstract funds' not actually deposited at the Clearing=20
House, but acknowledged as being available should variation or original=20
margin be required. The CTA has no control over these funds. All monetary=20
transactions must be executed by the Clearing House, and must be authorized=20
by the investor. The CTA does have the ability to execute trades at an other=
=20
trading house - such as Enron, through a contractual document called an=20
International Uniform Give-Up Agreement. We have quite a few hundred of thes=
e=20
agreements in NY. Essentially, all parties involved in the execution of a=20
trade - the CTA, the Investor, the Executing Broker and the Clearing House,=20
agree to allow the CTA to trade wherever he/she wishes and Give-Up that trad=
e=20
to the Investor's Clearing House. Since every regulated trade must ultimatel=
y=20
clear the respective exchange, for a CTA to trade OTC and Swap agreements,=20
would require prior notification to an investor that his/her money may be=20
required as collateral against such a trade, and would be required to be=20
deposited at Enron. A Hedge Fund has greater flexibility to trade such=20
instruments since in the majority of instances a Hedge Fund does exert=20
control over the funds it manages. A Hedge Fund typically structures its=20
investment vehicles as Off-Shore limited partnership funds. As such the Hedg=
e=20
fund has direct control over the underlying assets and can move those assets=
=20
to wherever they may be required - if investing via Enron On-Line, it would=20
move the assets to Enron, for example.

